parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel gauge can cause the rider to be misled about the fuel level, leading to unexpected engine stalling, stranding, and potentially dangerous situations on busy highways and bridges.
symptoms: The fuel gauge reads full then sticks at halfway
the fuel gauge drops to empty when the tank is not empty
the fuel gauge shows fuel when the tank is empty
the fuel gauge is intermittent
the fuel gauge does not work at all
the low fuel light comes on unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear brake light switch can cause a severe brake fluid leak, leading to a loss of rear brake pressure, which can result in accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Smoke or burning smell from underneath the motorcycle
no rear brake pressure
brake fluid leak
brake light switch burned or melted
repeated brake failure
loss of control of rear brake pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake fluid leaks can cause a loss of brake pressure, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: Brake fluid leak from the clutch and brake fluid reservoirs
repeated brake failure
loss of control of rear brake pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An intermittent gas gauge malfunction can cause the rider to be unaware of the fuel level, leading to unexpected engine stalling or running out of fuel.
symptoms: Gas gauge works sometimes and not others (random).

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear shock absorber can cause loss of vehicle control, reduced stability, and increased stopping distances, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle experiences uneven ride quality
the rear of the vehicle sags or leans
the vehicle makes unusual noises while driving
the shock absorber leaks fluid
the shock absorber mounting breaks or fails.
